document_data.History:
Valmir was originally a thief from [[Darromar]]. After a falling out with his guild, he moved around [[Tethyr]], where he learned some of [[the Art]]. Somehow, he impressed [[Merzan]] while on the run from a noble, who offered him an audition with [[Alaodin]], a few years before {{yearlink|1374}}. He had become [[Talieth]]'s lover{{cite book/Sentinelspire||24}} since.

[[Kerlis]], Valmir and [[Dren]] stayed behind to watch Berun and [[Lewan]] when Sauk decided to hunt down some [[yaqubi]], expecting them to be carrying gold.{{cite book/Sentinelspire||9}}

When in Sentinelspire, he employed a ''fireball'' to release Talieth and Sauk from their vine bindings at the [[Tower of the Sun]] on the night of [[Tarsakh 25]].{{cite book/Sentinelspire||38}} He survived the whole evening.{{cite book/Sentinelspire||41}}
